-- Military Must Help Maintain Civil Order, Fight Terrorism, Guo Boxiong Says
-- William Bi
-- 2010-07-17T00:39:49Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-17/military-must-help-maintain-civil-order-fight-terrorism-guo-boxiong-says.html

          
          
             China’s military must be on guard to
help the country maintain ethnic unity, fight terrorism and keep
social order, Guo Boxiong, vice chairman of the Central Military
Committee, said in a recent tour of soldiers stationed in the
country’s northeastern Xinjiang Autonomous Region, according to
a statement on the website of the Ministry of  National Defense
dated late yesterday.  
 To contact the reporter on this story:
